  "prompt": "Which are the best poems about India?",
  "response": "India has inspired a rich tapestry of poetry over the centuries, reflecting its diverse cultures, history, landscapes, and spirituality. Here are some celebrated poems about India:\n\n1. **\"Where the Mind is Without Fear\" by Rabindranath Tagore** - Part of his Nobel Prize-winning collection \"Gitanjali,\" this poem envisions a free and progressive India.\n\n2. **\"The Gift of India\" by Sarojini Naidu** - Sometimes referred to as the \"Nightingale of India,\" Naidu's poem pays tribute to the Indian soldiers who fought in World War I.\n\n3. **\"My Country Awake\" by Rabindranath Tagore** - A poem that calls for India to awaken to a future of freedom and enlightenment.\n\n4. **\"The Indian Weavers\" by Sarojini Naidu** - This poem reflects on the different stages of life through the metaphor of Indian weavers.\n\n5. **\"An Atlas of the Difficult World\" by Adrienne Rich** - Although not solely about India, Rich's poem includes powerful imagery and references to different parts of the world, including India, to explore themes of struggle and geopolitics.\n\n6. **\"A River\" by A.K. Ramanujan** - This poem contrasts the mythologized cultural perception of Indian rivers with their oft-ignored realities during drought and flood.\n\n7. **\"Night of the Scorpion\" by Nissim Ezekiel** - A vivid portrayal of Indian rural life and familial devotion in the face of crisis.\n\n8. **\"My Mother at Sixty-Six\" by Kamala Das** - An intimate reflection on familial bonds and the passage of time, capturing personal and universal themes.\n\nThese poems reflect various aspects of Indian life, history, and philosophy, offering readers a glimpse into the country's depth and diversity.",
